<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Mankind has been colonizing space for 1000 years, spreading itself out onto many planets and declaring independence from Earth. But now a powerful corporation backed by its overwhelming military force is looking to establish Earth} rule over the colony planets. One by one each colony has been forced to agree to an unfavorable treaty that gave the corporation ruling rights. Now it is planet Hornet's turn.
                  <br><br>The corporation has sent the warship Dante to force Hornet to comply. If Hornet refuses to sign the treaty, the Dante will unleash its powerful main guns to annihilate the planet. You are {Jutah Fate}, part of a group of special operatives sent to destroy the Dante by boarding it and wrecking it from the inside. {Silent Bomber} is a 3D action game that has you laying and detonating bombs. You follow the action from an overhead view, guiding Jutah through a series of mission objectives within the Dante warship.
                  <br><br>You can lay one or more bombs where you stand, or even drop lines of bombs while on the run. Bombs will remain inert until you detonate them, giving you a chance to lure enemies into your trap.
                  <br><br>You can also target enemies and throw bombs before detonating them. In addition to your "regular" bombs, you can also pick up and use several types of special weapons. Jutah has a health bar that drops each time he takes a hit. It is possible to boost his health level by collecting green health capsules, however. If Jutah's health is completely depleted the game is over, although players can choose to continue from the beginning of the level with full health.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Set in a dark, futuristic environment, Silent Bomber presents a world infested by rogue androids. These mechanical protagonists are overrunning the planet in a quest to wrestle dominance from its human inhabitants. Currently, the deranged droids inhabit the industrial areas of the planet, but their stranglehold is growing. As such, crack teams of explosive experts have been despatched to counter the threat.
                  <br><br>As one of the Silent Bombers, players are sent into a stunning 3-D world where the game's dark corridors and shadowy industrial locations play host to a number of deadly inhabitants. Using stealth, players must pick their way around each location with the express aim of eradicating all androids within each sector.
                  <br><br>Gameplay is based around a unique explosive system that sets up Silent Bomber's stall as a truly inventive game. Players use an intuitive targeting system to lock bombs on approaching androids. As soon as a robot walks into range, players can deploy a bomb directly at the oncoming foe or leave them in strategic positions and retreat before they detonate. Depending on the size of the adversary, several direct hits may be needed, presenting a real need for skill and tactical play on the bomber's part.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>SCI-FI & Futuristic themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

